description:
In this video, I’m sharing the 5 habits that help me thrive as a CEO—from waking up at 5AM to leading a team with purpose and launching our newest editorial shoot for Powder Melt.

You'll get an inside look at what really goes into building a brand—from personal growth to business strategy to creative execution.

Whether you’re a creative, an entrepreneur, or someone chasing your own goals, I hope this inspires you to lead with intention.

What’s your #1 daily habit that keeps you going? Let me know in the comments.

Y’ALL. I am SO excited to finally share our newest product with you—the Powder Melt Glass Setting Spray from ONE/SIZE! 😍 This isn’t your average setting spray… she MELTS your powder, sets your glam, and leaves you with that glass-skin fantasy that lasts up to 12 HOURS!

title: Coachella Vlog | PatrickStarrr
description:
Still on a high from one of the most magical weekends in the desert. I’ve been coming to Coachella for years, but this one hit different. To see ONE/SIZE have its own moment at the 818 Outpost was truly surreal.

What started as a dream has grown into something so much bigger—and sharing that with my friends, chosen family, and all of you means the world to me. Thank you to everyone who stopped by, showed love, and reminded me why we do this.

Coachella wasn’t just about the music or the glam (though there was plenty of that!)—it was about celebrating how far we’ve come. Hope you feel the joy through the screen.

Xoxo
PatrickStarrr

title: Waterproof Makeup Tutorial | Sweat-Proof, Pool-Proof, All Day Long! | PatrickStarrr
description:
Who’s ready for summer?! Festival season is upon us—and you already know we need makeup that can go all day (and night). So I had to put my glam to the test… and jumped straight into a pool. Yes. Full beat. No regrets. 💦

In this video, I’m sharing my ultimate waterproof makeup routine featuring some of my go-to longwear essentials—including the setting spray that keeps me On ‘Til Dawn 😉. Whether you’re heading to a festival, beach day, or just want your makeup to survive the heat, this look is locked and loaded.

Let’s stay glam all summer long.

xoxo
PatrickStarrr

title: 🌈I'm Gay | PatrickStarrr
description:
Pride 2021 is here! And this year, to celebrate and support the LGBTQ+ community, I’m joining forces with YouTube to launch the #GiveWithPride challenge, a donation campaign that aims to raise $500K for The Trevor Project. YouTube supports The Trevor Project’s mission to provide support, resources and suicide prevention for LGBTQ+ youth, so for the month of June, we will match any donations to the “Give With Pride” Challenge on YouTube up to $250K.*

If we reach our donation goal by June 19th, I will pledge to launch a highly anticipated stunt video which will air in YouTube Originals virtual pride celebration,YouTube Pride 2021 on June 25th here: bit.ly/YouTubePride2021. Be sure to tune in and donate if you can. Happy Pride! #YouTubePride2021

* The YouTube Give with Pride Challenge begins on June 1st, 2021 and ends on June 30th, 2021, with YouTube matching up to US$250,000 for every dollar donated to this “Give with Pride” campaign. Any additional donations made after the US$250,000 goal has been reached will not be matched by YouTube.

description:

Also got to support my friends Teni Panosian and makeupbyDenise for their Bobbi Brown lip crush collab and right after attend Kylie Jenner’s launch party for her new brand Kylie Skin! title: DIY HALLOWEEN MAC AND CHEESE | PatrickStarrr
description:

HAPPY HALLOWEEN! Brenda and Shirley here making Slime Mac and Cheese inspired by Green Glades from the game Best Fiends! Try this fun recipe at home for your next halloween party!

HALLOWEEN MAC AND CHEESE RECIPE

-----INGREDIENTS-----

୦ 1/4 cup unsalted butter
୦ 1/3 cup all-purpose flour
୦ 2 1/2 Cups of Milk
୦ 1/2 teaspoon sea salt
୦ 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper
୦ 1/4 teaspoon paprika
୦ 1 teaspoon onion powder
୦ 1 Tablespoon dry mustard powder
୦ pinch cayenne pepper
୦ 8 Ounces sharp white cheddar cheese
୦ Spinach
୦ Green food coloring 
୦ 1 Pound box pasta, cooked and drained 
୦ Cherry Tomatoes 
୦  Olives
୦  Cream Cheese

-----INSTRUCTIONS-----

1. Melt butter in a large pan/Dutch oven over medium-low heat
2. Add the flour and whisk to combine. Simmer, stirring constantly for 1 to 2 minutes
3.Pour in the milk and whisk to combine and remove all lumps
4.Add the salt, pepper, onion powder, paprika, cayenne, and mustard, stir to combine
5.Continue cooking until mixture starts to simmer, 6 to 8 minutes
6.Remove from heat and add the grated cheese. Stir until melted and completely combined
7.Add the spinach, stir to combine. Add a few drops of green food coloring if desired
8.Add the drained pasta and stir until completely coated
9.Add your cut Olives (slugs) use cream chees for eyes
10.Add your cut tomatoes shaped like lady bugs and add the black olive for the head and connect it using cream cheese

description:
Hey y'all!!! Brenda here with my assistant Shirley!! I made for y'all some tasty Halloween Hotdog Mummies and Shirley made Jalapeño Stuffed Mummies HERE https://youtu.be/nH73SeT15-U I hope y'all enjoy this recipe and try this at home! We have such a fun month ahead of us and we cant wait for y'all to recreate these for your next church event or Halloween Bash!!! Stay Humble and stay beautiful (well try!)

@NASTYBRENDA

HOTDOG MUMMIES RECIPE

-----INGREDIENTS-----
○ 1 can (8 oz) PillsburyTM refrigerated crescent dinner rolls or 1 can (8 oz) PillsburyTM
refrigerated Crescent Dough Sheet 
○ 10  large hot dogs
○ Cooking spray
○ Mustard, ketchup and mayonnaise

-----INSTRUCTIONS-----
1. Heat oven to 375°F.
2. If using crescent rolls: Unroll dough; separate at perforations, creating 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal. If using dough sheet: Unroll dough; cut into four rectangles.
3. With knife or kitchen scissors, cut each rectangle lengthwise into 10 pieces, making a
total of 40 pieces of dough. Slice cheese slices into quarters (1/2 slice cheese, cut in
half).
4. Wrap 4 pieces of dough around each hot dog and 1/4 slice of cheese to look like
"bandages," stretching dough slightly to completely cover hot dog. About 1/2 inch from one end of each hot dog, separate "bandages" so hot dog shows through for "face." On ungreased large cookie sheet, place wrapped hot dogs (cheese side down); spray dough lightly with cooking spray.
5. Bake 13 to 17 minutes or until dough is light golden brown and hot dogs are hot. With mustard, draw features on "face."

Hopefully this video inspires you to START living your life! Have Courage and be kind! 

I love you so so much!

Thank you so much for all your love and support. On my youtube channel, I want to empower you to be whatever you want to be. 

I started this makeup certification website because I was receiving so many questions and emails about the makeup industry. I want to offer those who are interested in this business, an opportunity to learn and interact with me! The difference between youtube and this website- is that I am able to send you makeup products in my custom BOX that are my personal favorites - directly from BRANDS to ME to YOU! 

I know this is not for everyone. I myself am self taught. However, I do know that there are those out there that would like to learn in depth makeup 1000%. 

Thank you for subscribing to my channel! If you are interested in starting your own YouTube channel...what are you waiting for?! JUST DO IT! You got this. We all start from somewhere- now is the time to embark on your own Cinderella Story! 

I love you all! 

xoxo
PatrickStarrr

title: Getting Kicked Out of IMATS | PatrickStarrr
description:
Hey Everyone! This is a little story time video of my IMATS NYC Experience. I am in no way wanting to bash or degrade Imats in any way. I love Imats so much. Imats is the place where makeup pros and enthusiasts can come together and share passion for makeup and artistry. Last year was my first time I attended Imats. I understand it is not the place for meet and greets. Manny and I decided to have our #redballoonmeetup outside for 2 hours and then proceed inside to work with a makeup company. We had NO idea the turnout inside would be so crazy! We were asked to move to a photo spot...then asked to leave. At that moment, I was so flustered and overwhelmed with how the security was yelling at everyone. It was honestly so unexpected at once, I did not mean to lash out at IMATS itself on social media. I understand Imats is not equipped with the means of hosting a massive meet and greet. I know that a large crowd is a hazard and not safe for others. I was just disappointed at how the message was delivered and overwhelmed at the same time with everyone that showed up to say hello!

Imats was once the place where bloggers, artists and makeup enthusiasts could gather and share a love for makeup. As of now, I am not planning on attending Imats next year. In my Cinderella Story, thats where my journey began as PatrickStarrr. 

I thank you all so much for the love and support. Manny and I were bawlinggggggg and crying with your stories and love. Im so happy we got meet and chit chat! I hope to meet you at one of the next shows! 

I will be at DragConLA, BeautyConLA, PhamexpoLA, Orlando Premiere Hair Show, GenBeautyNYC and BeautyConNYC!

I hope you all understand this video. Again, this video was not meant to bash imats...it was to simply share my experience this year!

LOVE YOU!
PatrickStarrr
